      "Card Type": "Legendary Land",
      "Description": "If Gemstone Caverns is in your opening hand and you're not playing first, you may begin the game with Gemstone Caverns in play with a luck counter on it. If you do, remove a card in your hand from the game.\r\n<br>\r\nT: Add 1 to your mana pool. If Gemstone Caverns has a luck counter on it, instead add one mana of any color to your mana pool.",
      "Artist": "Martina Pilcerova",
      "TCGplayer Tip": "Modeled after Tsuyoshi Fujita's design submission for the 2005 Magic: The Gathering Invitational, once folks saw Gemstone Caverns—then dubbed \"Unluckyman's Paradise\"—they were clamoring for it to see print. Tsuyoshi Fujita didn't win the 2005 Magic: The Gathering Invitational, but his design resonated so well with players that for the first and only time, Wizards of the Coast made an exception and sent two Invitational submissions to print."
